Method 4: Check /etc/X11/default-display-manager
Open a terminal.

Run the following command:
cat /etc/X11/default-display-manager

The output will show the default display manager.
If it's something like /usr/sbin/gdm3, you are using Wayland. 
If it's /usr/sbin/lightdm or /usr/sbin/gdm, you are likely using Xorg.
